genresAdvancedInfo.name: manitoba country
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Manitoba country is a subgenre of country music that originated in the Canadian province of Manitoba. It is characterized by its upbeat tempo, catchy melodies, and lyrics that often reflect the rural lifestyle and natural beauty of the province. Manitoba country artists often incorporate elements of folk and rock music into their sound, creating a unique blend of styles that is both traditional and modern. The genre has a dedicated following in Manitoba and beyond, and continues to evolve and grow.
